. Just have found the reason and the workaround.
If none of your classes injects it through Inject annotation, then it wont be listed in the mappings, and getInstance will fail.
@ahmednasir91 try this as workaround:
public class SomeClass {
    @Inject @Named("BOOKING") GCMMessage bookingGcmMessage;
}
