ShanePhelan:
I had the same issue (and also needed multiDexEnabled) and fixed it by using the multi dex support library for older devices:
1. add 'com.android.support:multidex:1.0.1' to your gradle compile options
2. If you're extending the android.app.Application override the attachBaseContext method
   @Override
   protected void attachBaseContext(Context base) {
       super.attachBaseContext(base);
       MultiDex.install(this);
   }
3. If you're not extending then you need to add the MultiDexApplication to your manifest application:
   android:name="android.support.multidex.MultiDexApplication"
See here for more details MultiDex
Hope this helps someone as it had me stumped for a while!
.

